<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-16T20:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-16T20:34:00-05:00" n="736" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d736">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2642: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-17T10:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">August 17,
                                        1922—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 10:30
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>It is reported from Japanese sources that granting of control over the
                            Chinese Eastern Railway to the mythical Government of China is approved
                            by the Powers. I trust this report is incorrect. Russian interests would
                            be completely betrayed by such action. The Manchurian government is
                            Chang Tso-lin …</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>